  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Each option has the form 3(2)<sup>(expression)</sup> or 6(2)<sup><em>x</em></sup>. Since <em>g</em>(<em>x</em>) doubles each time <em>x</em> increases by 1 and <em>g</em>(0) = 3, the function is <em>g</em>(<em>x</em>) = 3(2<sup><em>x</em></sup>). Checking: <em>g</em>(0) = 3(1) = 3, <em>g</em>(1) = 3(2) = 6, <em>g</em>(2) = 3(4) = 12, <em>g</em>(3) = 3(8) = 24. Choice B models exponential decay. Choice C gives <em>g</em>(0) = 6, not 3. Choice D gives <em>g</em>(0) = 6.</p>",
